		<p>Sagan is correct as far as he goes, but he doesn&#8217;t tell us how evolution happened or how learning started with apes and not earlier with bacteria for example.  This leaves room for simple minded creationism to fill those gaps for the ignorant religionists.<br/>
Evolutionists today see evolution as a self-evolving process based on all creatures learning from experience, and very gradually managing to change their forms accordingly.<br/>
Accidents of nature help but they can&#8217;t do that complex building by themselves.</p>

